1
00:01:36,125 --> 00:01:40,583
The train to New Ikebukuro is
now arriving on Platform One.

2
00:01:40,666 --> 00:01:42,500
Please watch your
step when boarding

3
00:01:42,583 --> 00:01:44,958
and stand clear of
closing doors.

4
00:02:17,875 --> 00:02:19,875
The Tokyo Metro
New Marunouchi line

5
00:02:19,958 --> 00:02:22,458
would like to thank you
for riding with us today.

6
00:02:22,541 --> 00:02:25,250
This train is currently
bound for New Ikebukuro.

7
00:02:25,333 --> 00:02:27,625
We'd like to take a moment
to inform all passengers

8
00:02:27,708 --> 00:02:31,250
that Tokyo Metro is cooperating
fully with the nine pm curfew

9
00:02:31,333 --> 00:02:33,125
required by the
Tokyo Government's

10
00:02:33,208 --> 00:02:34,625
Youth Protection Act.

11
00:02:34,708 --> 00:02:38,416
This curfew applies to all
citizens under twenty years old.

12
00:02:38,500 --> 00:02:41,125
Minors may circulate
after the curfew provided

13
00:02:41,208 --> 00:02:44,500
they have an approved permit
or constant adult supervision.

14
00:02:44,583 --> 00:02:46,458
If you are without
the proper permit,

15
00:02:46,541 --> 00:02:49,458
please proceed to the nearest
staff member for assistance.

16
00:02:49,541 --> 00:02:52,083
Again, minors may
only circulate after nine

17
00:02:52,166 --> 00:02:55,000
with an approved permit
or adult supervision.

18
00:02:55,083 --> 00:02:56,250
If you need assistance,

19
00:02:56,333 --> 00:02:58,875
please proceed to the
nearest staff member.

20
00:04:20,791 --> 00:04:24,000
Shall I eat you now
or play with you first?

21
00:05:30,541 --> 00:05:33,583
The train to New Ikebukuro
is arriving on Platform One.

22
00:05:33,666 --> 00:05:34,791
Please wait behind
the white line

23
00:05:34,875 --> 00:05:36,833
until the train comes
to a complete stop.

24
00:06:11,958 --> 00:06:12,916
Go figure.

25
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:15,958
They're not so subtle this time.

26
00:06:16,041 --> 00:06:17,041
Ready to head out?

27
00:06:17,125 --> 00:06:18,375
Not yet. Gimmie a sec.

28
00:06:19,708 --> 00:06:20,666
He's not there.

29
00:06:20,750 --> 00:06:21,750
He ran off.

30
00:06:21,833 --> 00:06:22,791
What?

31
00:06:22,875 --> 00:06:23,833
Another group.

32
00:06:23,916 --> 00:06:25,291
They saw him somewhere else.

33
00:06:25,375 --> 00:06:26,666
Let's go, then.

34
00:07:55,583 --> 00:07:56,750
Hello?

35
00:07:58,916 --> 00:08:00,500
Who are you?

36
00:08:42,250 --> 00:08:44,541
Destruction of target confirmed.

37
00:08:44,625 --> 00:08:46,083
Two witnesses.

38
00:08:46,166 --> 00:08:48,458
Recovery team, you're up.

39
00:08:54,208 --> 00:08:55,291
It's dead!

40
00:08:55,375 --> 00:08:57,041
It's totally been killed!

41
00:09:05,291 --> 00:09:06,791
Hey.

42
00:09:06,875 --> 00:09:08,500
Who the hell are you?

43
00:09:10,375 --> 00:09:11,875
Fujimura?

44
00:09:15,291 --> 00:09:16,750
Mana?

45
00:09:17,666 --> 00:09:18,791
Whoa.

46
00:09:18,875 --> 00:09:20,333
Are you okay?

47
00:09:24,250 --> 00:09:25,583
So that's it.

48
00:09:25,666 --> 00:09:27,291
That's an Elder Bairn?

49
00:09:27,375 --> 00:09:28,666
Elder Bairn.

50
00:09:28,750 --> 00:09:30,000
What are you doing out here?

51
00:09:30,083 --> 00:09:31,750
Matsuo. Hi.

52
00:09:31,833 --> 00:09:34,000
Fuji, we gotta roll!

53
00:09:34,083 --> 00:09:34,916
Right!

54
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:36,333
I got ya.

55
00:09:48,875 --> 00:09:49,791
Not good!

56
00:09:49,875 --> 00:09:51,250
Hurry!

57
00:10:04,875 --> 00:10:06,041
Move it.

58
00:10:06,708 --> 00:10:07,625
Who is she?

59
00:10:07,708 --> 00:10:08,416
I don't know.

60
00:10:08,500 --> 00:10:09,833
We should go.

61
00:10:11,833 --> 00:10:13,250
Damn it!

62
00:10:26,625 --> 00:10:29,083
Witnesses are fleeing by car.

63
00:10:29,166 --> 00:10:31,208
In pursuit, now.

64
00:10:31,291 --> 00:10:33,291
Ground squads, make your move.

65
00:10:39,708 --> 00:10:40,291
Hurry!

66
00:10:40,375 --> 00:10:41,416
They're right there!

67
00:10:42,416 --> 00:10:44,208
Then tell me where
the hell I need to go!

68
00:10:49,375 --> 00:10:50,500
Come in, Sirrut!

69
00:10:50,583 --> 00:10:51,666
It's Fujimura!

70
00:10:51,750 --> 00:10:52,666
Come in!

71
00:10:52,750 --> 00:10:54,291
There's a Tower
copter chasing us!

72
00:10:54,375 --> 00:10:55,041
Please!

73
00:10:55,125 --> 00:10:55,875
Help us!

74
00:10:55,958 --> 00:10:57,416
Yanagi!!

75
00:10:57,500 --> 00:10:58,500
Fujimura.

76
00:10:58,583 --> 00:11:00,000
You need to calm down...

77
00:11:01,583 --> 00:11:02,750
Yeah. Okay.

78
00:11:02,833 --> 00:11:04,041
Stand by.

79
00:11:04,125 --> 00:11:06,041
I'll have your route
for you in just a minute.

80
00:11:06,125 --> 00:11:07,916
Try to go ahead and
transfer any information

81
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:10,375
you've already gathered
in the meantime, all right?

82
00:11:10,458 --> 00:11:11,041
'Kay.

83
00:11:11,125 --> 00:11:12,166
I'll do what I can.

84
00:11:12,250 --> 00:11:13,750
Tsuki.

85
00:11:13,833 --> 00:11:16,416
You think you can get into the
transportation system networks?

86
00:11:16,500 --> 00:11:18,000
Yep.

87
00:11:18,083 --> 00:11:21,083
Wonderful, and what about the
Department of Motor Vehicles?

88
00:11:21,166 --> 00:11:22,708
I can do that.

89
00:11:25,125 --> 00:11:26,208
Mister Mogari.

90
00:11:26,291 --> 00:11:27,958
Do you approve?

91
00:11:31,583 --> 00:11:32,875
Yes.

92
00:11:57,625 --> 00:11:58,541
Right there!

93
00:11:58,625 --> 00:11:59,041
Turn right!

94
00:11:59,125 --> 00:11:59,958
Turn right!

95
00:12:00,041 --> 00:12:00,875
I can't!

96
00:12:00,958 --> 00:12:02,333
It's a one way street!

97
00:12:02,416 --> 00:12:04,166
Oh, sorry.

98
00:12:06,625 --> 00:12:07,916
Okay, awesome.

99
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,750
It looks like they've
finally got a route for us.

100
00:12:09,833 --> 00:12:10,875
We're good to go!

101
00:12:10,958 --> 00:12:12,708
Turn right up here.

102
00:12:12,791 --> 00:12:13,541
Yeah, right there!

103
00:12:13,625 --> 00:12:14,750
Right at the light

104
00:12:25,583 --> 00:12:26,416
Where are you going?

105
00:12:26,500 --> 00:12:28,041
Shut, up!

106
00:12:33,958 --> 00:12:36,708
So, I think we
might be off route.

107
00:12:36,791 --> 00:12:39,000
Yeah, I didn't have
much of a choice!

108
00:12:40,333 --> 00:12:41,208
Gimmie a sec.

109
00:12:41,291 --> 00:12:42,500
Look, you guys!

110
00:12:44,875 --> 00:12:45,541
What the hell?

111
00:12:45,625 --> 00:12:47,166
They're behind us again!

112
00:12:48,625 --> 00:12:50,791
I need something!

113
00:12:50,875 --> 00:12:52,791
Yanagi, help!

114
00:12:52,875 --> 00:12:54,416
Keep going straight ahead.

115
00:12:54,500 --> 00:12:56,291
Whatever you do,
don't slow down!

116
00:12:56,375 --> 00:12:57,333
Hurry!

117
00:12:58,750 --> 00:13:01,416
Okay, don't
blame me if we crash!

118
00:13:13,333 --> 00:13:14,250
You got 'em?

119
00:13:14,333 --> 00:13:15,541
Yep.

120
00:13:31,708 --> 00:13:33,666
They should be good to go now.

121
00:13:41,583 --> 00:13:43,708
I'm guessing we
should keep running.

122
00:14:00,625 --> 00:14:02,041
For the blood.

123
00:14:02,125 --> 00:14:03,916
I'm fine, thank you.

124
00:14:07,875 --> 00:14:10,666
Is that man dead?

125
00:14:15,291 --> 00:14:17,833
The important thing
is we're all safe now.

126
00:14:17,916 --> 00:14:20,625
My poor car has had
the crap beat out of it.

127
00:14:20,708 --> 00:14:22,541
I'm so sorry, baby girl.

128
00:14:22,625 --> 00:14:24,583
'Twas a noble sacrifice.

129
00:14:25,708 --> 00:14:28,958
I'm Mana Hiiragi.

130
00:14:29,041 --> 00:14:30,041
So, um.

131
00:14:30,125 --> 00:14:30,916
What's your name?

132
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:32,125
What?

133
00:14:32,208 --> 00:14:34,583
I thought this girl
was a friend of yours.

134
00:14:35,875 --> 00:14:37,166
No.

135
00:14:37,250 --> 00:14:40,625
But she... she saved me.

136
00:14:40,708 --> 00:14:42,500
From that thing.

137
00:14:42,583 --> 00:14:43,708
Seriously?

138
00:14:43,791 --> 00:14:44,583
She saved you?

139
00:14:44,666 --> 00:14:46,083
From the Tower's Elder Bairn?

140
00:14:48,166 --> 00:14:49,166
Tell me.

141
00:14:49,250 --> 00:14:51,125
What do you know
about the Elder Bairns?

142
00:14:51,208 --> 00:14:52,208
I know nothing.

143
00:14:52,291 --> 00:14:53,416
What's your problem lady?

144
00:14:53,500 --> 00:14:54,541
Let him go!

145
00:14:54,625 --> 00:14:55,708
No.

146
00:14:55,791 --> 00:14:56,791
So this Tower.

147
00:14:56,875 --> 00:14:58,500
Where is it?

148
00:14:58,583 --> 00:14:59,916
What do you know?

149
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:01,125
I don't know anything.

150
00:15:01,208 --> 00:15:02,833
I wish I could tell you.

151
00:15:02,916 --> 00:15:05,458
That's what we've
been trying to find out!

152
00:15:13,333 --> 00:15:14,791
He's telling the truth.

153
00:15:14,875 --> 00:15:17,708
Our goal is to find out
what the Tower is up to.

154
00:15:17,791 --> 00:15:19,750
Guess you've got
something against them?

155
00:15:19,833 --> 00:15:21,916
You mind telling
us what that is?

156
00:15:24,125 --> 00:15:26,333
And, while you're at it.

157
00:15:26,416 --> 00:15:28,708
What happened
back there, anyway?

158
00:15:28,791 --> 00:15:31,583
How the hell did that thing die?

159
00:15:31,666 --> 00:15:34,791
It died because I killed it.

160
00:15:39,791 --> 00:15:41,708
Oh-kay.

161
00:15:41,791 --> 00:15:43,541
What was your name again?

162
00:15:50,041 --> 00:15:51,416
It's HQ.

163
00:15:51,500 --> 00:15:53,333
Maybe it's Yanagi.

164
00:15:55,291 --> 00:15:57,000
Hello, Saya Kisaragi.

165
00:15:58,291 --> 00:15:59,666
Fumito Nanahara.

166
00:15:59,750 --> 00:16:02,000
You want him dead, right?

167
00:16:02,083 --> 00:16:03,666
Fumito?

168
00:16:09,541 --> 00:16:12,166
I'd be happy to meet with you.

169
00:16:12,250 --> 00:16:15,208
Perhaps you and
I can discuss the matter.

170
00:16:26,250 --> 00:16:29,916
There's a reward for the victor.

171
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:34,333
And a punishment for the loser.

172
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:50,291
Excuse me, sir.

173
00:16:51,791 --> 00:16:54,791
The Governor's office is
requesting a meeting with you.

174
00:16:54,875 --> 00:16:56,458
They'd like to discuss the
measures they're prepared

175
00:16:56,541 --> 00:16:59,958
to take against last month's
Youth Protection Act Violators.

176
00:17:01,333 --> 00:17:04,250
Things will be so much easier
when you become governor.

177
00:17:04,333 --> 00:17:05,958
Then, I won't have
to waste my time

178
00:17:06,041 --> 00:17:07,541
on these ridiculous meetings.

179
00:17:07,625 --> 00:17:09,083
Don't you agree, Yuka?

180
00:17:09,166 --> 00:17:11,291
Yes, sir, one hundred percent.

181
00:17:12,708 --> 00:17:14,833
How old are you again?

182
00:17:14,916 --> 00:17:17,250
I'll be twenty-eight this year.

183
00:17:17,333 --> 00:17:19,666
Isn't it amusing how you
were a high school girl

184
00:17:19,750 --> 00:17:21,958
up until only six months ago?

185
00:17:22,041 --> 00:17:23,291
Although, I'm sure
you'd rather forget

186
00:17:23,375 --> 00:17:26,166
about that particular
unpleasantness.

187
00:17:26,250 --> 00:17:27,833
Indeed, I would.

188
00:17:27,916 --> 00:17:29,875
Thank you for understanding.

189
00:17:29,958 --> 00:17:33,166
Also, about your meeting with
the US Ambassador later today.

190
00:17:33,250 --> 00:17:35,250
They're requesting
to see you earlier.

191
00:17:36,708 --> 00:17:39,250
It seems like that
happens a lot these days.

192
00:17:39,333 --> 00:17:41,166
Everyone wants to change things.

193
00:17:41,250 --> 00:17:44,250
If you ask me, given the
influence of our corporation,

194
00:17:44,333 --> 00:17:47,000
Seventh Heaven, as well as
the secret you and your clan

195
00:17:47,083 --> 00:17:50,125
have been keeping in
order to maintain peace.

196
00:17:50,208 --> 00:17:53,333
You deserve far more than
you've been getting, sir.

197
00:17:53,416 --> 00:17:55,416
You're so ambitious.

198
00:17:55,500 --> 00:17:56,958
Mister Nanahara?

199
00:17:57,875 --> 00:18:00,708
Yes, what is it, Kuto?

200
00:18:00,791 --> 00:18:03,000
I have an update on our lab
escapee.

201
00:18:03,083 --> 00:18:04,666
It's been terminated, sir.

202
00:18:06,416 --> 00:18:08,583
The subway cleanup
is complete, as well.

203
00:18:08,666 --> 00:18:13,041
But unfortunately, there were
two witnesses to the death.

204
00:18:13,125 --> 00:18:15,416
Don't tell me they escaped.

205
00:18:15,500 --> 00:18:18,291
I've already dealt with the men
who allowed them to get away.

206
00:18:19,500 --> 00:18:22,541
Next time, I'll be
sure to go myself.

207
00:18:22,625 --> 00:18:24,208
I don't know.

208
00:18:24,291 --> 00:18:26,375
You may not be up to it.

209
00:18:36,625 --> 00:18:38,708
Saya is here now.

210
00:19:33,500 --> 00:19:35,458
If you're finished, shall we go?

211
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:01,458
What's wrong?

212
00:20:01,541 --> 00:20:03,375
Follow me, please.

213
00:20:11,291 --> 00:20:12,666
Come in.

214
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:20,208
Mana, I understand; thank you.

215
00:20:20,291 --> 00:20:21,875
No, thank you.

216
00:20:21,958 --> 00:20:24,416
Welcome, Saya Kisaragi.

217
00:20:24,500 --> 00:20:26,250
I'm Kuroto Mogari.

218
00:20:26,333 --> 00:20:27,208
Are you?

219
00:20:27,291 --> 00:20:29,083
How do you know my name?

220
00:20:30,375 --> 00:20:31,916
Ukishima.

221
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:34,625
An experiment
was performed there.

222
00:20:34,708 --> 00:20:37,416
During which, everyone
was reportedly killed.

223
00:20:37,500 --> 00:20:39,083
Have you heard of it?

224
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:47,375
Judging from the pictures,

225
00:20:47,458 --> 00:20:50,583
it was a violent
and brutal massacre.

226
00:21:02,708 --> 00:21:04,166
However.

227
00:21:04,250 --> 00:21:07,833
One person was fortunate
enough to survive the ordeal.

228
00:21:11,875 --> 00:21:15,750
That person was
you, Saya Kisaragi.

229
00:21:19,250 --> 00:21:20,291
Clearly.

230
00:21:20,375 --> 00:21:22,458
And how exactly did
you find this out?

231
00:21:22,541 --> 00:21:24,250
Itsuki sent it to me.

232
00:21:26,916 --> 00:21:30,250
You knew him by the name,
Itsuki Tomafusa, correct?

233
00:21:30,333 --> 00:21:32,083
He hacked the Tower's cameras

234
00:21:32,166 --> 00:21:34,791
and managed to get a
few images out to us.

235
00:21:34,875 --> 00:21:38,125
Without him, we wouldn't
have known the truth.

236
00:21:38,208 --> 00:21:40,166
Was he a part of Sirrut?

237
00:21:40,250 --> 00:21:43,875
He never worked with the core
of this team, directly; no.

238
00:21:43,958 --> 00:21:46,750
But technically,
he was a member.

239
00:21:46,833 --> 00:21:48,541
What happened to him?

240
00:21:48,625 --> 00:21:50,250
He died.

241
00:21:52,083 --> 00:21:53,250
I knew it.

242
00:21:53,333 --> 00:21:55,333
He was a participant in
the Ukishima experiment.

243
00:21:55,416 --> 00:21:57,875
His goal was to try
and expose The Tower.

244
00:21:57,958 --> 00:21:59,625
Tower?

245
00:21:59,708 --> 00:22:01,375
The name of the
actual organization

246
00:22:01,458 --> 00:22:04,125
led by Fumito Nanahara.

247
00:22:04,208 --> 00:22:06,083
On the surface,
he's something else.

248
00:22:06,166 --> 00:22:08,708
CEO of a company
known as Seventh Heaven.

249
00:22:10,916 --> 00:22:12,916
It's an impressive,
massive corporation

250
00:22:13,000 --> 00:22:16,083
and has significant
global presence.

251
00:22:16,166 --> 00:22:17,333
Not surprisingly,

252
00:22:17,416 --> 00:22:20,125
he has many connections
politically, as well.

253
00:22:20,208 --> 00:22:22,541
It's widely accepted that
he was directly involved

254
00:22:22,625 --> 00:22:24,791
with the new
Youth Protection Act.

255
00:22:24,875 --> 00:22:29,166
In reality, his public persona
is just smoke and mirrors,

256
00:22:29,250 --> 00:22:31,291
a redirection of attention.

257
00:22:31,375 --> 00:22:34,000
Away from the Tower?

258
00:22:34,083 --> 00:22:35,458
That's correct.

259
00:22:35,541 --> 00:22:37,375
Fumito has been
using Seventh Heaven

260
00:22:37,458 --> 00:22:41,333
and the Tower to achieve
a very specific objective.

261
00:22:41,416 --> 00:22:42,541
And that would be?

262
00:22:42,625 --> 00:22:45,416
I wish I knew,
but unfortunately,

263
00:22:45,500 --> 00:22:47,583
we aren't entirely certain.

264
00:22:47,666 --> 00:22:50,000
But, what we do know
is that numerous people

265
00:22:50,083 --> 00:22:52,500
are being killed to fulfill it.

266
00:22:52,583 --> 00:22:55,375
Hundreds, maybe more.

267
00:22:55,458 --> 00:22:57,375
We've learned creatures
called Elder Bairns

268
00:22:57,458 --> 00:22:59,625
are somehow a part
of this thing, too.

269
00:22:59,708 --> 00:23:02,625
And, how do you know
all this information?

270
00:23:02,708 --> 00:23:03,541
Simple.

271
00:23:03,625 --> 00:23:04,791
I did research.

272
00:23:04,875 --> 00:23:08,791
Using all my resources:
time, money and power.

273
00:23:08,875 --> 00:23:09,958
But why?

274
00:23:10,041 --> 00:23:13,166
Because Fumito
Nanahara is pure evil.

275
00:23:13,250 --> 00:23:16,625
