00:53:33,041 --> 00:53:35,500
Being too cautious
only makes you stand out.

808
00:53:35,583 --> 00:53:37,583
Oh yeah, I guess
that makes sense.

809
00:53:38,791 --> 00:53:40,250
Did you know about this?

810
00:53:40,333 --> 00:53:41,375
About what?

811
00:53:41,458 --> 00:53:42,833
About this school.

812
00:53:42,916 --> 00:53:45,541
Did you know that it was
connected to Seventh Heaven?

813
00:53:46,500 --> 00:53:47,791
Yeah.

814
00:53:47,875 --> 00:53:49,125
There's a plaque
the school made

815
00:53:49,208 --> 00:53:50,875
to thank them for
their donations.

816
00:53:50,958 --> 00:53:53,083
And also, the teachers
are always talking

817
00:53:53,166 --> 00:53:54,958
about it like nonstop.

818
00:53:56,416 --> 00:54:00,000
I really wanted to
drop out, but I didn't.

819
00:54:03,333 --> 00:54:04,666
Mana!

820
00:54:06,041 --> 00:54:07,000
You made it!

821
00:54:07,083 --> 00:54:07,791
Oh.

822
00:54:07,875 --> 00:54:09,000
Yeah.

823
00:54:09,083 --> 00:54:10,916
I figured you'd
skip this assembly.

824
00:54:11,000 --> 00:54:13,208
It's like the middle
of winter break, y'know?

825
00:54:13,291 --> 00:54:16,041
So how's it been going
living all by yourself?

826
00:54:16,125 --> 00:54:17,583
You doing okay?

827
00:54:17,666 --> 00:54:19,208
Yeah.

828
00:54:19,291 --> 00:54:21,208
I heard about what
happened to your dad.

829
00:54:21,291 --> 00:54:22,541
I'm so sorry.

830
00:54:22,625 --> 00:54:24,000
We're glad you're
doing well, though.

831
00:54:24,083 --> 00:54:24,791
Oh.

832
00:54:24,875 --> 00:54:25,583
Thank you.

833
00:54:25,666 --> 00:54:27,041
Good to see you all.

834
00:54:28,375 --> 00:54:29,791
Let's go.

835
00:54:38,875 --> 00:54:40,375
Hey, lucky us!

836
00:54:40,458 --> 00:54:42,958
Looks like they're not going to
divide us up by classes today.

837
00:54:43,041 --> 00:54:44,000
Um.

838
00:54:44,083 --> 00:54:45,666
That's what they
would normally do.

839
00:54:45,750 --> 00:54:47,833
What did those girls mean?

840
00:54:47,916 --> 00:54:49,208
About your father.

841
00:54:51,500 --> 00:54:52,500
Just asking.

842
00:54:52,583 --> 00:54:53,541
Never mind.

843
00:54:54,958 --> 00:54:57,541
Everyone, please be quiet...

844
00:54:57,625 --> 00:55:01,000
We will now begin today's
very special lecture.

845
00:55:01,083 --> 00:55:04,208
Please welcome
Mister Fumito Nanahara.

846
00:55:06,500 --> 00:55:07,375
From Seventh Heaven?

847
00:55:07,458 --> 00:55:08,875
Seriously?

848
00:55:08,958 --> 00:55:10,666
So, that's why they wouldn't
let us bring in our phones.

849
00:55:10,750 --> 00:55:12,333
I wonder why he's talking to us.

850
00:55:33,208 --> 00:55:34,125
What?

851
00:55:35,333 --> 00:55:36,875
Please remain calm.

852
00:55:36,958 --> 00:55:38,458
Obey the staff's instructions,

853
00:55:38,541 --> 00:55:41,666
and evacuate the hall
in an orderly fashion.

854
00:55:44,083 --> 00:55:45,916
Saya, we have to get out!

855
00:55:46,000 --> 00:55:47,333
Come on!

856
00:55:56,666 --> 00:55:57,750
Mana!

857
00:55:57,833 --> 00:55:59,208
What's going on down there?

858
00:55:59,291 --> 00:56:00,791
I-I don't know!

859
00:56:00,875 --> 00:56:02,916
I heard screams
just after the bell.

860
00:56:03,000 --> 00:56:04,750
I can't tell. I have no idea!

861
00:56:04,833 --> 00:56:06,875
But their position
hasn't moved at all.

862
00:56:11,916 --> 00:56:14,333
It's been too long, Saya.

863
00:56:16,000 --> 00:56:17,208
Saya!

864
00:56:26,333 --> 00:56:29,458
Fumito!!!

865
00:56:36,125 --> 00:56:37,250
Saya.

866
00:56:37,333 --> 00:56:39,416
You came all this way for me.

867
00:56:39,500 --> 00:56:40,916
I'm flattered.

868
00:56:41,000 --> 00:56:43,041
And yet, I must apologize.

869
00:56:43,125 --> 00:56:44,666
I'm sure you understand.

870
00:56:44,750 --> 00:56:47,416
You're so strong;
I had to take precautions.

871
00:56:47,500 --> 00:56:52,166
But I wonder, will you at
least play with me awhile?

872
00:57:06,250 --> 00:57:07,750
So close.

873
00:57:07,833 --> 00:57:09,458
Why?

874
00:57:09,541 --> 00:57:10,125
Saya!

875
00:57:11,250 --> 00:57:12,083
Saya!

876
00:58:35,083 --> 00:58:36,041
Saya!

877
00:58:44,750 --> 00:58:46,000
Get down!

878
00:58:54,625 --> 00:58:55,833
Saya.

879
00:58:57,250 --> 00:58:58,208
Saya!

880
00:58:59,750 --> 00:59:01,375
Saya!

881
00:59:01,458 --> 00:59:02,291
Matsuo?

882
00:59:02,375 --> 00:59:03,333
What?

883
00:59:05,000 --> 00:59:07,041
Let's get them out of there!

884
00:59:07,125 --> 00:59:08,291
All right.

885
00:59:09,791 --> 00:59:11,958
Hang on to what you got!

886
00:59:16,083 --> 00:59:17,291
You're bleeding.

887
00:59:49,958 --> 00:59:51,208
Saya.

888
01:00:27,250 --> 01:00:27,875
Mana.

889
01:00:27,958 --> 01:00:28,916
Let's go!

890
01:00:29,000 --> 01:00:30,041
'Kay.

891
01:00:44,583 --> 01:00:46,291
I will go.

892
01:00:46,375 --> 01:00:48,708
The rest of you
recover it immediately.

893
01:00:59,583 --> 01:01:01,791
Saya, please move!

894
01:01:01,875 --> 01:01:03,375
I think I can open it.

895
01:01:05,666 --> 01:01:07,166
So, you're Saya.

896
01:01:10,583 --> 01:01:11,750
What's wrong?

897
01:01:11,833 --> 01:01:13,666
Are you in pain?

898
01:01:13,750 --> 01:01:15,791
You're a freak,
just like that monster.

899
01:01:15,875 --> 01:01:17,083
Shut up!

900
01:01:32,375 --> 01:01:33,541
Saya!

901
01:01:33,625 --> 01:01:35,291
Don't worry about me; go!

902
01:01:37,375 --> 01:01:38,416
You're done.

903
01:01:48,041 --> 01:01:50,666
It's a shame you
can't kill humans.

904
01:01:55,666 --> 01:01:56,833
I got it!

905
01:02:00,250 --> 01:02:01,750
If you could,

906
01:02:01,833 --> 01:02:04,916
you might have a better chance
at protecting your friends.

907
01:02:13,583 --> 01:02:15,166
Get in!

908
01:02:15,250 --> 01:02:16,916
Come on, let's go!

909
01:02:28,875 --> 01:02:30,250
She needs a doctor!

910
01:02:36,208 --> 01:02:38,666
Unfortunately, she fled.

911
01:02:38,750 --> 01:02:40,083
What a shame.

912
01:02:41,583 --> 01:02:44,666
We recovered the blood
per your previous orders.

913
01:02:44,750 --> 01:02:47,750
I'll take it to the lab as
soon as we're done here.

914
01:02:47,833 --> 01:02:49,666
Nicely done, Kuto.

915
01:03:02,166 --> 01:03:06,125
Basically, the entire
thing was a set up.

916
01:03:06,208 --> 01:03:08,250
I'm sorry.

917
01:03:08,333 --> 01:03:10,416
Tsuki.

918
01:03:10,500 --> 01:03:12,708
This wasn't your fault at all.

919
01:03:13,875 --> 01:03:15,833
I confirmed the
information provided

920
01:03:15,916 --> 01:03:18,666
as well as approved the plan.

921
01:03:18,750 --> 01:03:21,541
It's my responsibility.

922
01:03:21,625 --> 01:03:23,375
It's cool.

923
01:03:23,458 --> 01:03:24,708
Well.

924
01:03:24,791 --> 01:03:27,166
I'm just glad everyone
made it out in one piece.

925
01:03:27,250 --> 01:03:28,000
Yeah.

926
01:03:28,083 --> 01:03:29,708
Except for my car, that is.

927
01:03:29,791 --> 01:03:32,083
She's wrecked again!

928
01:03:32,166 --> 01:03:34,333
Another noble sacrifice.

929
01:03:34,416 --> 01:03:37,333
Well, considering somebody
actually did get hurt.

930
01:03:37,416 --> 01:03:39,625
I guess it's not
that big of a deal.

931
01:03:39,708 --> 01:03:41,875
Right?

932
01:03:41,958 --> 01:03:43,250
Yeah, I mean,
I thought you didn't

933
01:03:43,333 --> 01:03:45,833
even like Saya,
but it's whatever, man.

934
01:03:45,916 --> 01:03:48,791
Look, I can't ignore that
she was protecting Mana.

935
01:03:48,875 --> 01:03:52,166
She could have just left her
there to die if she wanted.

936
01:03:52,250 --> 01:03:54,541
I don't mind changing
my opinion, bro.

937
01:03:54,625 --> 01:03:57,375
Not if that's what
she's really like.

938
01:03:57,458 --> 01:03:58,500
Where is Saya?

939
01:03:58,583 --> 01:04:00,875
She said no doctors,
so Mana got mad

940
01:04:00,958 --> 01:04:04,458
and ran down the hall after
her; I imagine to her room.

941
01:04:04,541 --> 01:04:07,041
That was a high
tech electronic lock.

942
01:04:07,125 --> 01:04:09,416
Mana's the one who
opened it, right?

943
01:04:09,500 --> 01:04:11,791
Seems that way.

944
01:04:11,875 --> 01:04:12,958
You mean.

945
01:04:13,041 --> 01:04:14,625
Mana hacked something?

946
01:04:14,708 --> 01:04:16,750
That she did.

947
01:04:16,833 --> 01:04:19,375
And in like no time at all, too.

948
01:04:19,458 --> 01:04:20,625
That's good news.

949
01:04:20,708 --> 01:04:21,916
Our other genius hacker

950
01:04:22,000 --> 01:04:24,000
is proving rather
impressive herself.

951
01:04:24,083 --> 01:04:25,583
Of course she is!

952
01:04:25,666 --> 01:04:27,750
Mana is incredible!

953
01:04:27,833 --> 01:04:30,416
I learned from her;
she's the best.

954
01:04:30,500 --> 01:04:32,625
I'm not nearly as good.

955
01:04:34,333 --> 01:04:38,083
If anything, this could
help her regain confidence.

956
01:04:38,166 --> 01:04:39,416
I hope.

957
01:04:45,541 --> 01:04:47,500
Stop!

958
01:04:47,583 --> 01:04:49,958
I said stop!

959
01:04:50,041 --> 01:04:52,833
There's no way you're fine
after getting hurt like that!

960
01:04:52,916 --> 01:04:55,416
It's not as bad
as it looks, Mana.

961
01:04:55,500 --> 01:04:56,708
Saya!

962
01:05:06,916 --> 01:05:08,458
I'm really sorry.

963
01:05:10,875 --> 01:05:13,666
Don't be; there's
nothing to be sorry for.

964
01:05:16,458 --> 01:05:18,583
I don't want this.

965
01:05:18,666 --> 01:05:21,458
I don't want it to happen again.

966
01:05:21,541 --> 01:05:23,250
Not because of me.

967
01:05:28,125 --> 01:05:29,708
I really am alright.

968
01:05:29,791 --> 01:05:31,250
The wounds are healing.

969
01:05:37,666 --> 01:05:39,208
They really are.

970
01:05:40,916 --> 01:05:42,625
But how?

971
01:05:42,708 --> 01:05:44,041
Whatever the reason.

972
01:05:44,125 --> 01:05:46,416
What's important is I'm fine.

973
01:05:46,500 --> 01:05:48,458
Do you understand?

974
01:05:51,458 --> 01:05:54,375
Why did you say "again"?

975
01:05:54,458 --> 01:05:56,666
Has something like
this happened before?

976
01:06:08,166 --> 01:06:09,000
Sorta.

977
01:06:09,083 --> 01:06:10,333
My mom died when I was little,

978
01:06:10,416 --> 01:06:13,791
so it's just been me and
my dad for the most part.

979
01:06:13,875 --> 01:06:16,708
He was really awful
at cooking and stuff.

980
01:06:16,791 --> 01:06:18,291
But he always did
his absolute best

981
01:06:18,375 --> 01:06:20,833
to make something
I'd at least eat.

982
01:06:20,916 --> 01:06:24,208
He was always so
busy with his job.

983
01:06:24,291 --> 01:06:27,500
He still found a way to cook
for me everyday, though.

984
01:06:28,791 --> 01:06:29,750
His job?

985
01:06:29,833 --> 01:06:31,208
Newspaper reporter.

986
01:06:33,916 --> 01:06:36,333
He liked the old
fashioned newspapers,

987
01:06:36,416 --> 01:06:38,625
printed and all of that.

988
01:06:38,708 --> 01:06:41,208
When he'd been drinking,
he liked to say:

989
01:06:41,291 --> 01:06:45,541
"What a reporter needs is
curiosity and inquisitiveness."

990
01:06:45,625 --> 01:06:50,250
He taught me to take an interest
in anything and everything.

991
01:06:50,333 --> 01:06:51,625
And most importantly,

992
01:06:51,708 --> 01:06:54,875
he told me not to let
other people decide for me.

993
01:06:54,958 --> 01:06:56,833
"You should always take
care of your own research

994
01:06:56,916 --> 01:06:58,458
and make your own decisions."

995
01:06:58,541 --> 01:07:01,125
He had a bunch of
quotes like that about life.

996
01:07:01,208 --> 01:07:03,416
His favorite was, "When you
decide to do something,

997
01:07:03,500 --> 01:07:05,791
you should follow it
through until the end."

998
01:07:08,166 --> 01:07:09,291
A year ago.

999
01:07:09,375 --> 01:07:11,958
He had an idea; he'd
focus his next article

1000
01:07:12,041 --> 01:07:15,000
on an exclusive
about Seventh Heaven.

1001
01:07:15,083 --> 01:07:17,166
Eventually, pressure
came from higher up,

1002
01:07:17,250 --> 01:07:19,708
and the project was cancelled.

1003
01:07:19,791 --> 01:07:22,125
But my dad refused to quit.

1004
01:07:22,208 --> 01:07:24,583
He said he would
write the article anyway.

1005
01:07:24,666 --> 01:07:26,833
He wanted to find out the truth.

1006
01:07:29,333 --> 01:07:30,875
I wanted to help him,

1007
01:07:30,958 --> 01:07:33,333
so I conducted some
research of my own.

1008
01:07:36,291 --> 01:07:39,375
It helped that I was pretty
good with computers, too.

1009
01:07:42,583 --> 01:07:44,583
I hacked into
Seventh Heaven's systems

1010
01:07:44,666 --> 01:07:48,250
and discovered they were hiring
a lot of people out of the blue.

1011
01:07:48,333 --> 01:07:54,041
People who, not much later,
were reported missing.

1012
01:07:54,125 --> 01:07:58,125
I also found out something
called The Tower was involved.

1013
01:07:58,208 --> 01:08:01,625
Although, I wasn't sure how.

1014
01:08:01,708 --> 01:08:03,125
Dad took the proof I'd gathered

1015
01:08:03,208 --> 01:08:07,583
and said he was gonna
meet with Fumito Nanahara.

1016
01:08:07,666 --> 01:08:11,416
He thanked me for
helping him and left.

1017
01:08:11,500 --> 01:08:13,458
And then.

1018
01:08:13,541 --> 01:08:15,500
He never came back.

1019
01:08:17,500 --> 01:08:20,583
If I hadn't helped him,
then my dad wouldn't--

1020
01:08:20,666 --> 01:08:23,250
He hasn't come back,
and it's all my fault.

1021
01:08:26,833 --> 01:08:31,750
I came here cause.
I wanted to find my dad.

1022
01:08:31,833 --> 01:08:34,083
But, I was afraid
of what I might find,

1023
01:08:34,166 --> 01:08:36,708
so I stopped hacking altogether.

1024
01:08:36,791 --> 01:08:40,041
What if he...
What if he's dead?

1025
01:08:40,125 --> 01:08:44,791
I-I don't think I can
make it without him.

1026
01:08:53,750 --> 01:08:55,500
What about you?

1027
01:08:55,583 --> 01:08:57,541
Your father?

1028
01:08:57,625 --> 01:09:00,250
I don't have one.

1029
01:09:00,333 --> 01:09:02,750
But I knew a man who
was like a father to me.

1030
01:09:06,166 --> 01:09:08,166
I never thought
I would miss him.

1031
01:09:12,916 --> 01:09:15,291
How do you manage
to be so strong?

1032
01:09:17,541 --> 01:09:21,041
Your father and I share
the same philosophy.

1033
01:09:21,125 --> 01:09:24,375
Whatever I start, I see
through to the bitter end.

1034
01:09:24,458 --> 01:09:26,458
No matter what, I finish it.

1035
01:09:26,541 --> 01:09:28,875
I don't give myself a choice.

1036
01:09:28,958 --> 01:09:33,000
I do it because
I have to, so I can be me.

1037
01:09:35,458 --> 01:09:37,625
Now it makes sense.

1038
01:09:37,708 --> 01:09:38,958
Why I couldn't leave you.

1039
01:09:39,041 --> 01:09:42,208
Why I wanted to be near you.

1040
01:09:42,291 --> 01:09:43,916
We're a lot alike.

1041
01:09:44,000 --> 01:09:45,791
You and me.

1042
01:09:45,875 --> 01:09:47,666
We're lonely.

1043
01:10:00,083 --> 01:10:01,166
Nothing about what happened

1044
01:10:01,250 --> 01:10:02,916
at the high school
is showing up.

1045
01:10:03,000 --> 01:10:04,916
Big surprise, huh?

1046
01:10:05,000 --> 01:10:05,875
Yeah, right.

1047
01:10:05,958 --> 01:10:07,000
Assholes.

1048
01:10:08,458 --> 01:10:10,583
Mana and Saya
are still back there.

1049
01:10:10,666 --> 01:10:12,208
They haven't come out yet.

1050
01:10:12,291 --> 01:10:14,083
She was hurt pretty bad.

1051
01:10:14,166 --> 01:10:17,125
I bet Mana is
taking care of her.

1052
01:10:17,208 --> 01:10:19,791
Saya will be back
to gloomy in no time.

1053
01:10:21,583 --> 01:10:23,291
Good morning, everyone.

1054
01:10:23,375 --> 01:10:24,666
Good morning!

1055
01:10:24,750 --> 01:10:25,416
Hey!

1056
01:10:25,500 --> 01:10:27,083
It's about time!

1057
01:10:27,166 --> 01:10:28,416
Sorry.

1058
01:10:28,500 --> 01:10:30,000
We were up late last night.

1059
01:10:32,958 --> 01:10:34,291
Good morning, Tsuki.

1060
01:10:38,875 --> 01:10:40,000
Mana!

1061
01:10:43,416 --> 01:10:46,083
I'm sorry the stuff
I found out was wrong.

1062
01:10:46,166 --> 01:10:48,250
I'm sorry, Saya.

1063
01:10:48,333 --> 01:10:50,958
You didn't mislead us
on purpose, did you?

1064
01:10:51,041 --> 01:10:53,541
No, I would never do that.

1065
01:10:53,625 --> 01:10:54,625
No.

1066
01:10:54,708 --> 01:10:57,000
That's good to hear.

1067
01:10:57,083 --> 01:10:59,416
Then you have nothing
to apologize for.

1068
01:11:04,041 --> 01:11:06,666
Are you... Are you hurt?

1069
01:11:06,750 --> 01:11:07,625
No.

1070
01:11:07,708 --> 01:11:08,583
You mean it?

1071
01:11:08,666 --> 01:11:10,000
Yes.

1072
01:11:10,083 --> 01:11:11,208
That's nice.

1073
01:11:11,291 --> 01:11:13,916
I'm glad that you're all right.

1074
01:11:18,666 --> 01:11:19,458
So.

1075
01:11:19,541 --> 01:11:21,375
I, um, just... Uh.

1076
01:11:21,458 --> 01:11:23,375
I think I might have gotten
the wrong impression of you,

1077
01:11:23,458 --> 01:11:25,583
so what a relief I was wrong.

1078
01:11:25,666 --> 01:11:28,375
If that was supposed to
be an apology, it was crap.

1079
01:11:28,458 --> 01:11:30,333
I didn't ask you!

1080
01:11:31,916 --> 01:11:33,083
Anyway!

1081
01:11:33,166 --> 01:11:35,375
Thank you for saving Mana.

1082
01:11:35,458 --> 01:11:36,666
You're awesome!

1083
01:11:39,833 --> 01:11:40,875
Hey.

1084
01:11:40,958 --> 01:11:42,083
She just ignored me!

1085
01:11:42,166 --> 01:11:43,375
Can you blame her?

1086
01:11:44,583 --> 01:11:46,041
You guys.

1087
01:11:46,125 --> 01:11:48,375
I wanna talk to you
about something, okay?

1088
01:11:50,166 --> 01:11:51,250
Hacking?

1089
01:11:51,333 --> 01:11:52,333
Yes.

1090
01:11:54,083 --> 01:11:55,375
Are you sure?

1091
01:11:55,458 --> 01:11:56,666
You're ready?

1092
01:12:00,708 --> 01:12:02,333
I'm sure. Yes.

1093
01:12:02,416 --> 01:12:03,916
I'm never gonna
accomplish anything

1094
01:12:04,000 --> 01:12:05,875
if I just keep running away.

1095
01:12:05,958 --> 01:12:09,166
I'm ready, no matter
what the result is.

1096
01:12:10,541 --> 01:12:12,666
Very well.

1097
01:12:12,750 --> 01:12:13,958
Let's do it.

1098
01:12:16,500 --> 01:12:18,833
After the events
at the Tsuji Academy,

1099
01:12:18,916 --> 01:12:22,416
they now know all about
our organization's objective.

1100
01:12:22,500 --> 01:12:26,625
The Tower, Fumito, specifically,
will be coming for us.

1101
01:12:26,708 --> 01:12:30,541
We need to find the Tower's base
before they neutralize ours.

1102
01:12:30,625 --> 01:12:32,000
Everyone, bear that in mind.

1103
01:12:32,083 --> 01:12:33,208
Right.

1104
01:12:49,666 --> 01:12:52,750
You make a prisoner out
of everyone you meet.

1105
01:12:52,833 --> 01:12:54,916
At least that's
what the rumors say.

1106
01:12:58,208 --> 01:12:59,458
Well, they're wrong.

1107
01:12:59,541 --> 01:13:01,458
I don't do anything.

1108
01:13:06,416 --> 01:13:09,916
Ask, and it shall
be given to you.

1109
01:13:10,000 --> 01:13:11,458
Seek and find.

1110
01:13:11,541 --> 01:13:13,333
Knock and the door shall open.

1111
01:13:13,416 --> 01:13:14,833
That's what we're promised.

1112
01:13:14,916 --> 01:13:17,125
Just ask the right question.

1113
01:13:17,208 --> 01:13:19,041
And yet, we humans
are still forced

1114
01:13:19,125 --> 01:13:21,291
to find the answers ourselves...

1115
01:13:23,000 --> 01:13:24,083
Tell me.

1116
01:13:24,166 --> 01:13:26,875
Do you know what
your answer is, Saya?

1117
01:14:33,208 --> 01:14:35,500
I can't believe
you got this for me.

1118
01:14:35,583 --> 01:14:38,375
I just poured some of
what was already there.

1119
01:14:38,458 --> 01:14:39,916
Well, thank you.

1120
01:14:41,583 --> 01:14:42,625
Didn't you want any?

1121
01:14:42,708 --> 01:14:43,833
It wasn't for me.

1122
01:14:43,916 --> 01:14:45,125
That's not true.

1123
01:14:45,208 --> 01:14:47,208
Mister Mogari made it.

1124
01:14:47,291 --> 01:14:49,000
He said it was his way
of thanking all of us

1125
01:14:49,083 --> 01:14:50,958
for the work we've been doing.

1126
01:14:51,041 --> 01:14:53,833
He wanted to do something
for everyone, including you.

1127
01:15:06,375 --> 01:15:07,833
You aren't going to rest?

1128
01:15:07,916 --> 01:15:10,041
I have a feeling I'm
really close to finding them.

1129
01:15:10,125 --> 01:15:12,333
So I can't sleep, not yet.

1130
01:15:12,416 --> 01:15:15,541
See, this is kind of like my
version of the power you have.

1131
01:15:15,625 --> 01:15:17,875
Hacking is my weapon.

1132
01:15:17,958 --> 01:15:19,500
I understand.

1133
01:15:34,416 --> 01:15:35,541
What's going on?

1134
01:15:50,375 --> 01:15:51,791
I found it, Saya.

1135
01:15:53,541 --> 01:15:55,416
The Tower's headquarters.

1136
01:16:02,666 --> 01:16:04,666
You're sure it's the
Tokyo Bay Breakwater,

1137
01:16:04,750 --> 01:16:06,166
'cause that seems weird.

1138
01:16:06,250 --> 01:16:07,333
She's sure.

1139
01:16:08,833 --> 01:16:11,583
You should have seen
her; it was amazing.

1140
01:16:11,666 --> 01:16:12,666
The way she dodges walls

1141
01:16:12,750 --> 01:16:16,083
and pursues stuff
is almost godlike.

1142
01:16:16,166 --> 01:16:17,875
Well, then why
didn't you wake me up?

1143
01:16:17,958 --> 01:16:19,750
I enjoy godlike things.

1144
01:16:21,041 --> 01:16:24,083
I don't understand how;
there's nothing out there.

1145
01:16:24,166 --> 01:16:26,250
Well, not from an
address search, no.

1146
01:16:26,333 --> 01:16:28,083
But when you look at the
area from an aerial view,

1147
01:16:28,166 --> 01:16:30,041
it's a completely
different story.

1148
01:16:35,500 --> 01:16:36,625
Where?

1149
01:16:38,000 --> 01:16:39,166
I don't see anything.

1150
01:16:39,250 --> 01:16:41,625
They put false data
on the satellite image,

1151
01:16:41,708 --> 01:16:44,083
but all you have
to do is remove that.

1152
01:16:44,166 --> 01:16:45,375
Watch.

1153
01:16:45,458 --> 01:16:47,333
That's crazy!

1154
01:16:47,416 --> 01:16:49,416
Good job.

1155
01:16:49,500 --> 01:16:51,791
She truly is a gifted hacker.

1156
01:16:54,000 --> 01:16:55,750
Saya.

1157
01:16:55,833 --> 01:16:58,083
Are you ready to face Fumito?

1158
01:17:12,916 --> 01:17:15,375
I can't believe they
hid something this big.

1159
01:17:15,458 --> 01:17:17,833
Those Tower guys are good.

1160
01:17:17,916 --> 01:17:20,000
And we still managed to find it.

1161
01:17:20,083 --> 01:17:22,791
Guess that makes us better. Huh?

1162
01:17:24,916 --> 01:17:26,666
I would say that it does.

1163
01:17:26,750 --> 01:17:28,666
Um, about me not going with you.

1164
01:17:28,750 --> 01:17:29,750
You sure?

1165
01:17:29,833 --> 01:17:31,791
I'm sure.

1166
01:17:31,875 --> 01:17:33,875
I need you to help me from here.

1167
01:17:33,958 --> 01:17:35,750
If you go, then you'll die.

1168
01:17:35,833 --> 01:17:37,833
But Saya, what about you?

1169
01:17:37,916 --> 01:17:39,125
I'll be fine.

1170
01:17:39,208 --> 01:17:40,291
You've seen the truth.

1171
01:17:40,375 --> 01:17:42,166
Remember that.

1172
01:17:42,250 --> 01:17:44,125
Most injuries won't stop me.

1173
01:17:44,208 --> 01:17:46,333
Don't you have a
weapon to use, anyway?

1174
01:17:49,541 --> 01:17:50,916
Yeah, you're right.

1175
01:17:51,000 --> 01:17:53,208
And I still have to find my dad.

1176
01:17:58,708 --> 01:18:01,000
All we can do is support,
but we'll be here.

1177
01:18:01,083 --> 01:18:04,166
You can count on us, and you
ladies are ready, too, right?

1178
01:18:04,250 --> 01:18:06,666
Definitely; we're both
ready and standing by.

1179
01:18:12,291 --> 01:18:14,291
If something happens,
let us know.

1180
01:18:14,375 --> 01:18:16,541
We'll hold out as
long as we're able to.

1181
01:18:16,625 --> 01:18:19,458
If it gets bad, do
yourself a favor and run.

1182
01:18:21,083 --> 01:18:22,416
Thank you.

1183
01:18:27,833 --> 01:18:30,625
Okay, we're changing positions.

1184
01:19:16,875 --> 01:19:18,041
Where's the target?

1185
01:19:29,750 --> 01:19:31,250
Hey, it's goin' down.

1186
01:19:32,666 --> 01:19:33,833
Fuji.

1187
01:19:33,916 --> 01:19:36,625
Make sure we don't
lose sound with her, okay?

1188
01:19:36,708 --> 01:19:38,125
On it.

1189
01:19:43,916 --> 01:19:45,000
Hey, Tsuki.

1190
01:19:45,083 --> 01:19:47,166
Can you see what's
going on inside there?

1191
01:19:47,250 --> 01:19:48,208
Gimmie a sec.

1192
01:19:48,291 --> 01:19:49,666
Got the frequency!

1193
01:19:49,750 --> 01:19:51,208
Can you tell how
many there are?

1194
01:19:51,291 --> 01:19:52,500
Sure thing!

1195
01:20:18,208 --> 01:20:21,250
Saya, we have their
numbers and positions.

1196
01:20:21,333 --> 01:20:24,416
The farther you ascend,
the more they carry radios.

1197
01:20:24,500 --> 01:20:26,500
Fumito must be on the top floor.

1198
01:20:28,041 --> 01:20:30,083
You're wrong.

1199
01:20:30,166 --> 01:20:33,166
Fumito knows about things
that aren't entirely human.

1200
01:20:33,250 --> 01:20:35,916
Dangerous things
that don't use radios.

1201
01:20:36,000 --> 01:20:37,833
Where are the Elder Bairns?

1202
01:20:39,583 --> 01:20:41,750
What area has the fewest people?

1203
01:20:43,250 --> 01:20:44,208
The basement.

1204
01:20:44,291 --> 01:20:45,375
Then get me there.

1205
01:20:45,458 --> 01:20:46,583
Just a sec.

1206
01:21:05,083 --> 01:21:06,916
Nice trick, you bastard.

1207
01:21:09,500 --> 01:21:11,375
Saya?

1208
01:21:11,458 --> 01:21:13,000
Keep going.

1209
01:21:13,083 --> 01:21:14,208
Right.

1210
01:21:20,458 --> 01:21:22,916
I will never let you
reach Mister Nanahara.

1211
01:21:34,375 --> 01:21:37,750
You are pathetic, Saya Kisaragi.

1212
01:21:40,458 --> 01:21:44,833
Do not call me that name!

1213
01:21:52,875 --> 01:21:55,541
I have the route
to the basement!

1214
01:21:55,625 --> 01:21:56,750
From the elevators.

1215
01:21:56,833 --> 01:21:59,666
Take the door on the
right, far in the back.

1216
01:21:59,750 --> 01:22:01,166
Saya?

1217
01:22:02,541 --> 01:22:03,625
Kuto.

1218
01:22:03,708 --> 01:22:05,041
That should be enough.

1219
01:22:10,875 --> 01:22:11,833
Of course.

1220
01:22:11,916 --> 01:22:13,833
Thank you, Mister Nanahara.

1221
01:22:15,750 --> 01:22:16,916
It's time.

1222
01:22:17,000 --> 01:22:18,208
You will now witness the power

1223
01:22:18,291 --> 01:22:20,166
of the one who
will rule the world!

1224
01:22:20,250 --> 01:22:21,416
Behold.

1225
01:22:37,333 --> 01:22:39,916
Fumito!

1226
01:23:05,875 --> 01:23:07,250
I can't tell what's going on.

1227
01:23:07,333 --> 01:23:08,750
Get her out of there, Mana.

1228
01:23:08,833 --> 01:23:11,041
Listen, Saya, run
straight in front of you!

1229
01:23:11,125 --> 01:23:12,875
Then take the exit just ahead!

1230
01:23:28,875 --> 01:23:30,000
Good job.

1231
01:23:30,083 --> 01:23:31,041
Take your next left.

1232
01:23:39,208 --> 01:23:41,750
You'll be able to reach
the lowest lever from there.

1233
01:24:00,166 --> 01:24:01,458
Saya?

1234
01:24:01,541 --> 01:24:02,375
I'm fine.

1235
01:24:02,458 --> 01:24:03,583
I made it.

1236
01:24:51,458 --> 01:24:53,041
Good evening, Saya.

1237
01:24:53,125 --> 01:24:54,375
How are you?

1238
01:24:58,083 --> 01:24:59,541
What have you done?

1239
01:25:03,541 --> 01:25:04,875
What is this?

1240
01:25:06,375 --> 01:25:09,500
I don't. Stop.

1241
01:25:11,416 --> 01:25:13,208
Fumito.

1242
01:25:14,833 --> 01:25:15,833
Saya!

1243
01:25:15,916 --> 01:25:17,250
Saya, what's wrong?!

1244
01:25:17,333 --> 01:25:18,708
No!

1245
01:25:20,208 --> 01:25:21,333
Saya!

1246
01:25:21,416 --> 01:25:23,458
Saya!

1247
01:25:23,541 --> 01:25:24,916
Fuji!

1248
01:25:25,000 --> 01:25:26,000
It's no use!

1249
01:25:26,083 --> 01:25:27,708
I've lost the connection!

1250
01:25:32,291 --> 01:25:33,916
I'd prefer no interruptions,

1251
01:25:34,000 --> 01:25:36,000
now that we're finally together.

1252
01:25:36,083 --> 01:25:38,208
I had to shut down your radios.

1253
01:25:38,291 --> 01:25:40,000
I'm sure you understand.

1254
01:25:41,083 --> 01:25:43,416
I'm delighted
you came to see me.

1255
01:25:44,541 --> 01:25:48,000
Although, I do wish you hadn't
broken so many of my things.

1256
01:26:00,458 --> 01:26:01,375
Yes.

1257
01:26:01,458 --> 01:26:05,041
It's finally taken
effect, Kuroto.

1258
01:26:05,125 --> 01:26:08,375
I brought the
amount you requested.

1259
01:26:08,458 --> 01:26:10,375
It took long enough.

1260
01:26:10,458 --> 01:26:13,791
All that running,
and she's only down now.

1261
01:26:13,875 --> 01:26:15,666
What a freak.

1262
01:26:23,875 --> 01:26:25,166
The coffee.

1263
01:26:25,250 --> 01:26:26,708
No.

1264
01:26:29,875 --> 01:26:32,083
Will you tell me
now why I personally

1265
01:26:32,166 --> 01:26:34,500
had to put that
stuff in her coffee?

1266
01:26:34,583 --> 01:26:36,875
Your young assistants
are just so good.

1267
01:26:36,958 --> 01:26:40,541
They'd never imagine slipping
something bad into her drink.

1268
01:26:40,625 --> 01:26:42,166
Luckily, I had you.

1269
01:26:42,250 --> 01:26:44,291
"Good" is not your forte.

1270
01:26:46,708 --> 01:26:48,333
This doesn't work on humans.

1271
01:26:48,416 --> 01:26:51,666
It's for you and
you alone, my Saya.

1272
01:26:51,750 --> 01:26:54,333
You must be worried about
your little Sirrut friends.

1273
01:26:54,416 --> 01:26:55,833
They are gifted, aren't they?

1274
01:26:57,458 --> 01:27:00,083
In fact, you can thank them for
getting you to where you are.

1275
01:27:00,166 --> 01:27:02,375
You were too suspicious
to eat anything.

1276
01:27:02,458 --> 01:27:04,541
But you let your guard down.

1277
01:27:04,625 --> 01:27:06,666
With that coffee.

1278
01:27:06,750 --> 01:27:08,125
Who'd have imagined?

1279
01:27:08,208 --> 01:27:10,250
Those kids were useful.

1280
01:27:10,333 --> 01:27:14,083
Don't get the wrong idea:
I never lied to them per se.

1281
01:27:14,166 --> 01:27:17,875
All I did was just
use them a little.

1282
01:27:17,958 --> 01:27:20,791
Sirrut originated as
a small internet group.

1283
01:27:20,875 --> 01:27:24,583
They were full of all those
"more freedom in Tokyo" types.

1284
01:27:24,666 --> 01:27:25,833
I know what you're thinking;

1285
01:27:25,916 --> 01:27:28,041
I should've just ignored them.

1286
01:27:28,125 --> 01:27:30,208
But you can never predict
what someone on the internet

1287
01:27:30,291 --> 01:27:31,958
might do to people like us,

1288
01:27:32,041 --> 01:27:35,250
so I decided to keep
an eye on them myself.

1289
01:27:35,333 --> 01:27:38,958
I offered financial support and
became their mentor and patron.

1290
01:27:39,041 --> 01:27:41,500
They believed any and
every bit of information

1291
01:27:41,583 --> 01:27:45,208
I 'leaked' to them, which
made things very easy.

1292
01:27:45,291 --> 01:27:47,541
I was impressed with myself.

1293
01:27:47,625 --> 01:27:50,750
Eventually, they found
fascinating leads about you,

1294
01:27:50,833 --> 01:27:54,333
resulting in your
arrival in my mansion.

1295
01:27:54,416 --> 01:27:58,875
I admit, I never expected
Mana would find this place.

1296
01:27:58,958 --> 01:28:02,083
She is a talented girl.

1297
01:28:02,166 --> 01:28:04,833
But, I did immediately
let Fumito know

1298
01:28:04,916 --> 01:28:07,291
they had found him.

1299
01:28:07,375 --> 01:28:08,375
So then.

1300
01:28:08,458 --> 01:28:10,375
What's next, dear cousin?

1301
01:28:10,458 --> 01:28:12,375
You do have a plan, yes?

1302
01:28:12,458 --> 01:28:16,125
I still don't get why you spend
so much effort on that thing.

1303
01:28:16,208 --> 01:28:19,125
I spend effort
because Saya is special.

1304
01:28:19,208 --> 01:28:21,291
Yes, I suppose she must be.

1305
01:28:21,375 --> 01:28:24,333
You did dedicate all
of our resources to her.

1306
01:28:26,750 --> 01:28:29,875
Our arrangement was to
kill each other's families,

1307
01:28:29,958 --> 01:28:34,125
take control over The Tower,
and use the power we had stolen,

1308
01:28:34,208 --> 01:28:36,916
to seize control of
the world, correct?

1309
01:28:37,000 --> 01:28:37,666
Oh, yes.

1310
01:28:37,750 --> 01:28:39,000
That's right.

1311
01:28:39,083 --> 01:28:40,250
It's not over.

1312
01:28:40,333 --> 01:28:43,500
There's still more
glory, money, influence.

1313
01:28:43,583 --> 01:28:46,500
I do not crave such things.

1314
01:28:46,583 --> 01:28:50,458
My desire has
always been the world.

1315
01:28:50,541 --> 01:28:52,708
Of course, what was I thinking?

1316
01:28:52,791 --> 01:28:55,583
It's small, this world.

1317
01:28:55,666 --> 01:28:58,333
It really is quite small.

1318
01:28:58,416 --> 01:29:00,833
Isn't that right, Saya?

1319
01:29:00,916 --> 01:29:03,500
So this thing is
the world to you?

1320
01:29:12,041 --> 01:29:13,541
You let your guard down.

1321
01:29:13,625 --> 01:29:15,708
How sad.

1322
01:29:15,791 --> 01:29:19,041
You and your freak
will die here together.

1323
01:29:19,125 --> 01:29:21,250
I'll make it look as
though she killed you.

1324
01:29:21,333 --> 01:29:24,291
Then, everything will be mine.

1325
01:29:26,416 --> 01:29:28,791
That was terribly
rude, dear cousin.

1326
01:29:30,125 --> 01:29:31,916
How dare you judge!

1327
01:29:32,000 --> 01:29:34,583
You've always looked
down your nose at me.

1328
01:29:34,666 --> 01:29:36,291
And I've hated it!

1329
01:29:46,333 --> 01:29:46,791
No.

1330
01:29:46,875 --> 01:29:48,750
No!

1331
01:29:48,833 --> 01:29:51,375
And now, I'll take
back what I loaned to you.

1332
01:29:51,458 --> 01:29:53,375
Because you're ungrateful.

1333
01:29:54,916 --> 01:29:57,541
Fumito.

1334
01:29:57,625 --> 01:29:59,541
Can you feel her blood?

1335
01:30:01,791 --> 01:30:03,750
Watch him, Saya.

1336
01:30:03,833 --> 01:30:06,250
He is the Covenant in action.

1337
01:30:11,625 --> 01:30:15,833
All of that power you've
desired, dear cousin.

1338
01:30:15,916 --> 01:30:18,625
You will now have
the chance to feel.

1339
01:30:22,958 --> 01:30:24,375
Saya.

1340
01:30:24,458 --> 01:30:26,541
For generations, the
heads of the Mogari clan

1341
01:30:26,625 --> 01:30:28,333
have buried something.

1342
01:30:28,416 --> 01:30:29,666
Do you know where
they put the key

1343
01:30:29,750 --> 01:30:31,875
to controlling the
Elder Bairns?

1344
01:30:31,958 --> 01:30:34,541
It's hidden within them.

1345
01:30:34,625 --> 01:30:36,375
Your blood has power.

1346
01:30:36,458 --> 01:30:38,750
It is the sole thing that
can destroy the connection

1347
01:30:38,833 --> 01:30:40,750
we have with the Elder Bairns.

1348
01:30:43,333 --> 01:30:45,250
Fumito!

1349
01:30:53,708 --> 01:30:55,291
See, Saya?

1350
01:30:55,375 --> 01:30:57,041
It's as I thought.

1351
01:30:57,125 --> 01:30:59,291
Humans don't become it.

1352
01:30:59,375 --> 01:31:01,625
They are born to it.

1353
01:31:01,708 --> 01:31:03,875
You cannot kill humans.

1354
01:31:03,958 --> 01:31:05,166
You are not human.

1355
01:31:06,750 --> 01:31:09,083
The only things that
can satiate your hunger

1356
01:31:09,166 --> 01:31:14,500
are the Elder Bairns,
your own kind.

1357
01:31:14,583 --> 01:31:19,125
Did you know the number of
humans is always increasing,

1358
01:31:19,208 --> 01:31:23,000
but the number of Elder Bairns
has dropped dramatically.

1359
01:31:23,083 --> 01:31:26,541
There's hardly even a need
for the Shrovetide anymore.

1360
01:31:27,875 --> 01:31:29,083
Saya.

1361
01:31:29,166 --> 01:31:30,583
How old are you?

1362
01:31:30,666 --> 01:31:32,000
How many years?

1363
01:31:32,083 --> 01:31:34,250
How long will you live?

1364
01:31:34,333 --> 01:31:36,583
Does the Elder Bairns
decline concern you?

1365
01:31:36,666 --> 01:31:38,375
Do you worry at all
how you will survive

1366
01:31:38,458 --> 01:31:40,625
when they finally
become extinct?

1367
01:31:40,708 --> 01:31:42,208
It worries me.

1368
01:31:42,291 --> 01:31:45,250
I tried to create
Elder Bairns for you.

1369
01:31:45,333 --> 01:31:49,875
I used your blood,
and The Tower's magic.

1370
01:31:49,958 --> 01:31:51,791
But it didn't work.

1371
01:31:51,875 --> 01:31:54,416
No matter what I did.

1372
01:31:54,500 --> 01:31:58,041
They all ended up dying soon
after their transformation.

1373
01:31:58,125 --> 01:31:59,458
I did my best.

1374
01:31:59,541 --> 01:32:02,250
I experimented on
all types of people.

1375
01:32:02,333 --> 01:32:05,041
Practically anyone
I could get my hands on.

1376
01:32:09,125 --> 01:32:11,250
Mana, was it?

1377
01:32:11,333 --> 01:32:14,041
I saw the footage
from the Mogari mansion.

1378
01:32:14,125 --> 01:32:16,333
Her father was a reporter, yes?

1379
01:32:18,541 --> 01:32:20,333
He lasted longer than most...

1380
01:32:22,416 --> 01:32:24,875
But he ran away and died.

1381
01:32:24,958 --> 01:32:27,500
Not too long ago, in fact.

1382
01:32:27,583 --> 01:32:28,708
You knew him.

1383
01:32:31,083 --> 01:32:34,083
He was on the
same train you were.

1384
01:32:34,166 --> 01:32:36,625
Surely, you remember.

1385
01:32:36,708 --> 01:32:39,666
After all, you did kill him.

1386
01:33:02,458 --> 01:33:03,500
What the hell?

1387
01:33:13,583 --> 01:33:15,541
There's the true Saya.

1388
01:33:15,625 --> 01:33:17,500
In all her loveliness.

1389
01:33:17,583 --> 01:33:19,458
A reward for the victor.

1390
01:33:21,541 --> 01:33:24,250
This is the strongest
power that I can summon.

1391
01:33:24,333 --> 01:33:27,000
It's all for you, my, love.

1392
01:33:33,458 --> 01:33:37,500
Back then, all I could
do was run away from you.

1393
01:33:37,583 --> 01:33:39,500
Not now, Saya.

1394
01:34:41,875 --> 01:34:43,583
Is that an Elder Bairn?

1395
01:35:20,916 --> 01:35:23,208
Those eyes.

1396
01:35:23,291 --> 01:35:27,333
They're exactly as they were
when I shot you in the head.

1397
01:35:27,416 --> 01:35:29,541
So beautiful.

1398
01:35:29,625 --> 01:35:32,791
I want you, Saya.

1399
01:35:32,875 --> 01:35:35,708
Fumito!

1400
01:36:40,708 --> 01:36:42,291
Fumito.

1401
01:36:44,291 --> 01:36:47,083
Why did you do this?

1402
01:36:56,083 --> 01:36:58,458
Right here, Saya.

1403
01:36:58,541 --> 01:37:00,666
Fumito?

1404
01:37:00,750 --> 01:37:02,000
I told you.

1405
01:37:02,083 --> 01:37:04,541
It isn't easy.

1406
01:37:04,625 --> 01:37:06,791
I tried it on me
before anyone else.

1407
01:37:06,875 --> 01:37:12,250
I wanted to see, if I could
be like my beloved Saya.

1408
01:37:17,291 --> 01:37:19,166
I've been waiting for this.

1409
01:37:19,250 --> 01:37:22,333
To finally hold you.

1410
01:37:22,416 --> 01:37:24,541
Forgive me, Saya.

1411
01:37:24,625 --> 01:37:26,583
If I were still human.

1412
01:37:26,666 --> 01:37:33,916
Your curse would be lifted;
you would be free.

1413
01:37:34,000 --> 01:37:37,750
A reward for you, the victor.

1414
01:37:37,833 --> 01:37:39,541
And me?

1415
01:37:39,625 --> 01:37:43,291
I'll receive the
punishment as the loser.

1416
01:37:48,833 --> 01:37:53,708
You were supposed
to dodge that, Saya.

1417
01:37:53,791 --> 01:37:56,666
Now it feels like a reward.

1418
01:38:09,708 --> 01:38:15,375
And in the end, I am alone.

1419
01:38:15,458 --> 01:38:18,375
Always alone.

1420
01:38:33,541 --> 01:38:34,666
We can't see anything.

1421
01:38:34,750 --> 01:38:37,541
Cops are all over the place.

1422
01:38:37,625 --> 01:38:38,791
Right now they're only allowing

1423
01:38:38,875 --> 01:38:41,708
the emergency
vehicles to get through.

1424
01:38:41,791 --> 01:38:43,541
Yeah, we're stuck here, too.

1425
01:38:43,625 --> 01:38:46,000
We still can't get
ahold of Mister Mogari.

1426
01:38:47,166 --> 01:38:48,708
Um, excuse me.

1427
01:38:48,791 --> 01:38:50,333
Excuse me.

1428
01:39:08,500 --> 01:39:10,666
Most importantly,
I think we can all agree

1429
01:39:10,750 --> 01:39:14,500
what the youth really
need for growth is freedom.

1430
01:39:14,583 --> 01:39:18,458
Unnecessarily tying them down
will only invite rebellion.

1431
01:39:18,541 --> 01:39:20,958
Also, we must avoid
any circumstance

1432
01:39:21,041 --> 01:39:23,250
that would create
generational distrust...

1433
01:39:23,333 --> 01:39:25,291
So lady, how was your class?

1434
01:39:25,375 --> 01:39:26,750
Did you have fun?

1435
01:39:26,833 --> 01:39:27,833
Yeah.

1436
01:39:27,916 --> 01:39:30,041
I mean, I stayed the whole time.

1437
01:39:30,125 --> 01:39:32,000
Why don't you join a club?

1438
01:39:32,083 --> 01:39:33,958
Cause I'm not a nerd.

1439
01:39:34,041 --> 01:39:35,875
I have more fun here anyway.

1440
01:39:37,916 --> 01:39:39,208
Mana!

1441
01:39:40,500 --> 01:39:42,791
Hey, what's up?

1442
01:39:42,875 --> 01:39:43,875
I have to say,

1443
01:39:43,958 --> 01:39:45,458
I like how much
more relaxed things are

1444
01:39:45,541 --> 01:39:47,083
with this new governor.

1445
01:39:47,166 --> 01:39:48,208
At least the
internet restrictions

1446
01:39:48,291 --> 01:39:49,750
are lifted, you know?

1447
01:39:49,833 --> 01:39:51,541
The Youth Protection
Act is gone;

1448
01:39:51,625 --> 01:39:53,625
that's the most important thing.

1449
01:39:53,708 --> 01:39:56,000
Compared to back then,
this is heaven.

1450
01:39:59,166 --> 01:40:00,666
Almost heaven.

1451
01:40:00,750 --> 01:40:03,208
I wish Mister Mogari
was still here.

1452
01:40:04,625 --> 01:40:07,000
Cisnet was absorbed
by another company.

1453
01:40:07,083 --> 01:40:10,458
So, Seventh Heaven's executives
have all been replaced.

1454
01:40:10,541 --> 01:40:14,000
Even Fumito Nanahara
vanished from public life.

1455
01:40:14,083 --> 01:40:16,041
There's no telling
where Mister Mogari went,

1456
01:40:16,125 --> 01:40:18,250
but surely he's fine.

1457
01:40:20,000 --> 01:40:21,416
Oh, I'm sorry about that.

1458
01:40:21,500 --> 01:40:22,791
This got dark.

1459
01:40:22,875 --> 01:40:24,000
Sorry.

1460
01:40:25,500 --> 01:40:27,375
It's okay.

1461
01:40:27,458 --> 01:40:28,708
You know, thinking about it,

1462
01:40:28,791 --> 01:40:30,541
it's been like a
year and a half.

1463
01:40:30,625 --> 01:40:31,750
It's crazy.

1464
01:40:33,291 --> 01:40:34,833
I wonder.

1465
01:40:34,916 --> 01:40:36,083
Wonder what?

1466
01:40:36,166 --> 01:40:38,666
You do realize this is
all your fault, Matsuo!

1467
01:40:38,750 --> 01:40:40,333
How do you figure that?

1468
01:40:40,416 --> 01:40:41,625
You are such a brat!

1469
01:40:41,708 --> 01:40:43,541
Am not!

1470
01:40:43,625 --> 01:40:45,208
There they go again.

1471
01:40:46,666 --> 01:40:47,625
You think they'll get any better

1472
01:40:47,708 --> 01:40:49,625
when they get
married next month?

1473
01:40:49,708 --> 01:40:51,458
Nah, they'll never change.

1474
01:40:51,541 --> 01:40:53,250
I think that's why they work.

1475
01:40:53,333 --> 01:40:54,833
Hey, knock it off!

1476
01:40:54,916 --> 01:40:57,208
Can you two quit
fighting for once?

1477
01:40:57,291 --> 01:40:58,083
Okay.

1478
01:40:58,166 --> 01:40:59,583
Lucky for you, you're pretty.

1479
01:40:59,666 --> 01:41:01,125
Lucky for what?

1480
01:41:01,208 --> 01:41:02,625
You are such an idiot.

1481
01:41:02,708 --> 01:41:03,541
To be with you?

1482
01:41:03,625 --> 01:41:05,041
Never.

1483
01:41:05,125 --> 01:41:10,958
I wonder, why do I have the
feeling we'll see her again.

